rate these true Dutch treats into American celebrations.The book not only talks about the history and recipes of St. Nicholas Day celebrations, but also about Dutch specialties for Christmas and New Year's. Rose includes recipes for savory cookies and party treats as well as menus and recipes for the parties that might happen between the feast days. Divided into two parts, part one discusses the history of St. Nicholas, how he was brought to America and became Santa, and the other changes that have taken place here as well as in the Netherlands. The second part consists of 111 recipes that are easy to make and easy to love.Delicious December is for anyone interested in food and history, and those of Dutch descent will find many old favorites here, together with new, fresh ideas based on long traditions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aChristmas cooking. 0aCooking, Dutch. 0aDutch AmericansxSocial life and customs. 4aAmerican Studies : American Culture. 4aCultural Studies : Food. 4aHistory : American History. 4aHistory : History. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143844915940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438449159423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438449159/original  a978-3-11-149015-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles